    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Chief executives are more optimistic about the economy now than they have been in more than a year, according to the Conference Board's index of C.E.O. confidence for the first three months of 2007.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Chief executives are more optimistic about the economy now than they have been in more than a year, according to the Conference Board's index of C.E.O. confidence for the first three months of 2007.</p>
        <p>''The index shows there are a few more optimists than there are pessimists,'' Kenneth Goldstein, Conference Board economist, said. ''It's not that business confidence is shooting up through the roof.''</p>
        <p>ELIZABETH OLSON</p>
        <p>OPENERS: SUITS</p>
      </block>
